HEADWORD: Trilingual
<hw>Tri*lin"gual</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>trilinguis</ets>; <ets>tri-</ets> (see <er>Tri-</er>) +
<ets>lingua</ets> tongue, language. See <er>Lingual</er>.]</ety>
<def>Containing, or consisting of, three languages; expressed in three
languages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The much-noted Rosetta stone . . . bears upon its surface a
<qex>trilingual</qex> inscription.</q> <rj><qau>I.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trilinguar</ent>⟦br⟧
